Class StringGraph

java.lang.Object
StringGraph
All Implemented Interfaces:
Graph
public class StringGraph
extends java.lang.Object
implements Graph
Implementation of the Graph interface using an adjacency matrix.

  • Constructor Details

    • StringGraph

      public StringGraph()
      Default constructor sets initial capacity to 1. Note: This constructor can call the constructor that takes an initial capacity.

    • StringGraph

      public StringGraph​(int initCapacity)
      Parameterized constructor sets initial capacity to given capacity.
      Parameters:
      initCapacity - initial capacity for number of vertices
      Throws:
      java.lang.RuntimeException - if initialCapacity is less than 1.

    • StringGraph

      public StringGraph​(java.lang.String[] initVertices)
      Parameterized constructor that gives an initial set vertex labels. Constructs a graph with capacity equal to the number of labels and adds a vertex for each label given. No edges are added.
      Parameters:
      initVertices - An initial set of vertex labels.

    • StringGraph

      public StringGraph​(java.lang.String[] initVertices, java.lang.String[][] initEdges)
      Parameterized constructor that gives an initial set of vertex labels and edges. Constructs a graph with capacity equal to the number of labels, adds a vertex for each given label, and adds the specified edges. Note: This constructor can call the constructor that has a parameter of only vertex labels.
      Parameters:
      initVertices - An initial set of vertex labels.
      initEdges - An 2 x m array representing the edges of this graph.

    • toString4

      public java.lang.String toString4()
      Returns a string containing the adjacency matrix for this graph. The entire adjacency matrix is not necessarily included. Only rows and columns corresponding to vertices are provided. True values are shown as "T" and false values are shown as "=". The rows and columns are labeled with both the index as well as the vertex label.
      Returns:
      A string showing the adjacency matrix for this graph.

    • toString5

      private java.lang.String toString5()
      Returns a string containing the entire adjacency matrix. True values are shown as "T", false values are shown as "-". Note: The entire adjacency matrix is included, even if there are more rows/columns beyond the number of vertices.
      Returns:
      A string showing the entire adjacency matrix.
